    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e9ba6bd3_0831380d",
        "filename": "firmware/target/mips/ingenic_x1000/system-target.h",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 126,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000603
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-03-03T21:32:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "See my comments in system-x1000.c; we could use the /4 prescaler here with no meaningful loss.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 126,
        "startChar": 7,
        "endLine": 126,
        "endChar": 52
      },
      "revId": "1b9555859e46be85f1625e0c82f2bc6e6d71875f",
      "serverId": "583131e1-1a33-4f2b-b8ec-82434880f207",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "31a4e694_1341b729",
        "filename": "firmware/target/mips/ingenic_x1000/system-target.h",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 139,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000603
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-03-03T21:32:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If I\u0027m doing my math correctly, a 64-bit OST will take 24,372 years to wrap, even running at 24MHz.  So we probably don\u0027t need to worry about wrapping.\n\nAlso, it\u0027s best to add +1 to us to guarantee that we will always delay at least as long as the requested time.  (otherwise we could under-delay by a fraction of a us..  on the other hand, you\u0027re using 64-bit math, which probably makes up the difference and then some..)",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 137,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 139,
        "endChar": 33
      },
      "revId": "1b9555859e46be85f1625e0c82f2bc6e6d71875f",
      "serverId": "583131e1-1a33-4f2b-b8ec-82434880f207",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "eef3603c_5b44d81b",
        "filename": "firmware/target/mips/ingenic_x1000/system-target.h",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 145,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000603
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-03-03T21:32:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It\u0027s preferable to change this into a loop, each for 1000us.  This way we don\u0027t have to worry about math overflow in udelay().  (OTOH, 32-bit overflow occurs at 179s @ 24MHz..)",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 145,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 145,
        "endChar": 36
      },
      "revId": "1b9555859e46be85f1625e0c82f2bc6e6d71875f",
      "serverId": "583131e1-1a33-4f2b-b8ec-82434880f207",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "11e5655f_3dcf9026",
        "filename": "firmware/target/mips/ingenic_x1000/system-x1000.c",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 82,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000603
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-03-03T21:32:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Can you document the nominal clock speed these clock configurations result in?",
      "revId": "1b9555859e46be85f1625e0c82f2bc6e6d71875f",
      "serverId": "583131e1-1a33-4f2b-b8ec-82434880f207",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "30cd1b8b_5a774579",
        "filename": "firmware/target/mips/ingenic_x1000/system-x1000.c",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 131,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000603
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-03-03T21:32:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Do we really need full 24MHz resolution on OST2?  Why not cut it down to /4 to save a little bit of power?  (we\u0027ll still have 6 ticks per us, plenty of granularity)",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 131,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 131,
        "endChar": 43
      },
      "revId": "1b9555859e46be85f1625e0c82f2bc6e6d71875f",
      "serverId": "583131e1-1a33-4f2b-b8ec-82434880f207",
      "unresolved": true
    },
